		"description": "# Postman_collection_CAT_AS_A_SERVICE_CRUD\n\nPostman collection for the second challenge.\n\nIt contains the following HTTP requests to test the backend:\n\n---\n\n- **Req. 1: \"1_GET_ALL_CATS_DATA_BLOB_FORMAT\"**\n    \n\nGets all cats data in the database in a json format.\n\nNote: The cats are stored in BLOB (binary large objects).\n\n- **Req.2.1: \"2_GET_CAT_JSON_WITH_ID\"**\n    \n\nGets a specific cat (by id) in a json format (the image is in BLOB format).\n\n- **Req.2.2: \"2.2_GET_CAT_IMAGE_WITH_ID\"**\n    \n\nGets a specific cat (by id) but this time it shows the real cat image.\n\n- **Req.3: \"3_GET_RANDOM_CAT_IMAGE\"**\n    \n\nGets a random cat from the database, it displays the real cat image.\n\n- **Req.4:\"4_POST_CAT_DATA\"**\n    \n\nCreate a cat.\n\nInputs in the body:\n\n\\-> \"name\" (mandatory)\n\n\\-> \"metadata\" (optional)\n\n\\-> \"imageData\" (optional): this can be selected as a real image! Please check the instructions pdf for a step by step guide.\n\n\\-> mimeType (optional)\n\nOnly name is required (for testing purposes).\n\n- **Req. 5: \"5_DELETE_A_CAT_BY_ID\"**\n    \n\nDelete a cat by ID.\n\n- **Req.6: \"6_PUT_update_A_CAT_BY_ID\"**\n    \n\nUpdate a cat.\n\nFor more details please check the pdf with the instructions provided along with the code.\n\n---",
